2699 /* If weight not fully consumed, exit the polling mode */
2700 if (work_done < weight) {
2701 if (adapter->itr_setting & 3)
2702 e1000_set_itr(adapter);
2703 napi_complete_done(napi, work_done);
2704 if (!test_bit(__E1000_DOWN, &adapter->state)) {
2705 if (adapter->msix_entries)
2706 ew32(IMS, adapter->rx_ring->ims_val |
2707 E1000_IMS_OTHER);
2708 else
2709 e1000_irq_enable(adapter);
2710 }
2711 }
2712
2713 return work_done;
2714}
2715
2716static int e1000_vlan_rx_add_vid(struct net_device *netdev,
2717 __always_unused __be16 proto, u16 vid)
2718{
2719 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
2720 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2721 u32 vfta, index;
2722
2723 /* don't update vlan cookie if already programmed */
2724 if ((adapter->hw.mng_cookie.status &
2725 E1000_MNG_DHCP_COOKIE_STATUS_VLAN) &&
2726 (vid == adapter->mng_vlan_id))
2727 return 0;
2728
2729 /* add VID to filter table */
2730 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_HW_VLAN_FILTER) {
2731 index = (vid >> 5) & 0x7F;
2732 vfta = E1000_READ_REG_ARRAY(hw, E1000_VFTA, index);
2733 vfta |= BIT((vid & 0x1F));
2734 hw->mac.ops.write_vfta(hw, index, vfta);
2735 }
2736
2737 set_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans);
2738
2739 return 0;
2740}
2741
2742static int e1000_vlan_rx_kill_vid(struct net_device *netdev,
2743 __always_unused __be16 proto, u16 vid)
2744{
2745 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
2746 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2747 u32 vfta, index;
2748
2749 if ((adapter->hw.mng_cookie.status &
2750 E1000_MNG_DHCP_COOKIE_STATUS_VLAN) &&
2751 (vid == adapter->mng_vlan_id)) {
2752 /* release control to f/w */
2753 e1000e_release_hw_control(adapter);
2754 return 0;
2755 }
2756
2757 /* remove VID from filter table */
2758 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_HW_VLAN_FILTER) {
2759 index = (vid >> 5) & 0x7F;
2760 vfta = E1000_READ_REG_ARRAY(hw, E1000_VFTA, index);
2761 vfta &= ~BIT((vid & 0x1F));
2762 hw->mac.ops.write_vfta(hw, index, vfta);
2763 }
2764
2765 clear_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans);
2766
2767 return 0;
2768}
2769
2770/**
2771 * e1000e_vlan_filter_disable - helper to disable hw VLAN filtering
2772 * @adapter: board private structure to initialize
2773 **/
2774static void e1000e_vlan_filter_disable(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
2775{
2776 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
2777 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2778 u32 rctl;
2779
2780 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_HW_VLAN_FILTER) {
2781 /* disable VLAN receive filtering */
2782 rctl = er32(RCTL);
2783 rctl &= ~(E1000_RCTL_VFE | E1000_RCTL_CFIEN);
2784 ew32(RCTL, rctl);
2785
2786 if (adapter->mng_vlan_id != (u16)E1000_MNG_VLAN_NONE) {
2787 e1000_vlan_rx_kill_vid(netdev, htons(ETH_P_8021Q),
2788 adapter->mng_vlan_id);
2789 adapter->mng_vlan_id = E1000_MNG_VLAN_NONE;
2790 }
2791 }
2792}
2793
2794/**
2795 * e1000e_vlan_filter_enable - helper to enable HW VLAN filtering
2796 * @adapter: board private structure to initialize
2797 **/
2798static void e1000e_vlan_filter_enable(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
2799{
2800 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2801 u32 rctl;
2802
2803 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_HW_VLAN_FILTER) {
2804 /* enable VLAN receive filtering */
2805 rctl = er32(RCTL);
2806 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_VFE;
2807 rctl &= ~E1000_RCTL_CFIEN;
2808 ew32(RCTL, rctl);
2809 }
2810}
2811
2812/**
2813 * e1000e_vlan_strip_disable - helper to disable HW VLAN stripping
2814 * @adapter: board private structure to initialize
2815 **/
2816static void e1000e_vlan_strip_disable(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
2817{
2818 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2819 u32 ctrl;
2820
2821 /* disable VLAN tag insert/strip */
2822 ctrl = er32(CTRL);
2823 ctrl &= ~E1000_CTRL_VME;
2824 ew32(CTRL, ctrl);
2825}
2826
2827/**
2828 * e1000e_vlan_strip_enable - helper to enable HW VLAN stripping
2829 * @adapter: board private structure to initialize
2830 **/
2831static void e1000e_vlan_strip_enable(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
2832{
2833 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2834 u32 ctrl;
2835
2836 /* enable VLAN tag insert/strip */
2837 ctrl = er32(CTRL);
2838 ctrl |= E1000_CTRL_VME;
2839 ew32(CTRL, ctrl);
2840}
2841
2842static void e1000_update_mng_vlan(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
2843{
2844 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
2845 u16 vid = adapter->hw.mng_cookie.vlan_id;
2846 u16 old_vid = adapter->mng_vlan_id;
2847
2848 if (adapter->hw.mng_cookie.status & E1000_MNG_DHCP_COOKIE_STATUS_VLAN) {
2849 e1000_vlan_rx_add_vid(netdev, htons(ETH_P_8021Q), vid);
2850 adapter->mng_vlan_id = vid;
2851 }
2852
2853 if ((old_vid != (u16)E1000_MNG_VLAN_NONE) && (vid != old_vid))
2854 e1000_vlan_rx_kill_vid(netdev, htons(ETH_P_8021Q), old_vid);
2855}
2856
2857static void e1000_restore_vlan(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
2858{
2859 u16 vid;
2860
2861 e1000_vlan_rx_add_vid(adapter->netdev, htons(ETH_P_8021Q), 0);
2862
2863 for_each_set_bit(vid, adapter->active_vlans, VLAN_N_VID)
2864 e1000_vlan_rx_add_vid(adapter->netdev, htons(ETH_P_8021Q), vid);
2865}
2866
2867static void e1000_init_manageability_pt(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
2868{
2869 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2870 u32 manc, manc2h, mdef, i, j;
2871
2872 if (!(adapter->flags & FLAG_MNG_PT_ENABLED))
2873 return;
2874
2875 manc = er32(MANC);
2876
2877 /* enable receiving management packets to the host. this will probably
2878 * generate destination unreachable messages from the host OS, but
2879 * the packets will be handled on SMBUS
2880 */
2881 manc |= E1000_MANC_EN_MNG2HOST;
2882 manc2h = er32(MANC2H);
2883
2884 switch (hw->mac.type) {
2885 default:
2886 manc2h |= (E1000_MANC2H_PORT_623 | E1000_MANC2H_PORT_664);
2887 break;
2888 case e1000_82574:
2889 case e1000_82583:
2890 /* Check if IPMI pass-through decision filter already exists;
2891 * if so, enable it.
2892 */
2893 for (i = 0, j = 0; i < 8; i++) {
2894 mdef = er32(MDEF(i));
2895
2896 /* Ignore filters with anything other than IPMI ports */
2897 if (mdef & ~(E1000_MDEF_PORT_623 | E1000_MDEF_PORT_664))
2898 continue;
2899
2900 /* Enable this decision filter in MANC2H */
2901 if (mdef)
2902 manc2h |= BIT(i);
2903
2904 j |= mdef;
2905 }
2906
2907 if (j == (E1000_MDEF_PORT_623 | E1000_MDEF_PORT_664))
2908 break;
2909
2910 /* Create new decision filter in an empty filter */
2911 for (i = 0, j = 0; i < 8; i++)
2912 if (er32(MDEF(i)) == 0) {
2913 ew32(MDEF(i), (E1000_MDEF_PORT_623 |
2914 E1000_MDEF_PORT_664));
2915 manc2h |= BIT(1);
2916 j++;
2917 break;
2918 }
2919
2920 if (!j)
2921 e_warn("Unable to create IPMI pass-through filter\n");
2922 break;
2923 }
2924
2925 ew32(MANC2H, manc2h);
2926 ew32(MANC, manc);
2927}
2928
2929/**
2930 * e1000_configure_tx - Configure Transmit Unit after Reset
2931 * @adapter: board private structure
2932 *
2933 * Configure the Tx unit of the MAC after a reset.
2934 **/
2935static void e1000_configure_tx(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
2936{
2937 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
2938 struct e1000_ring *tx_ring = adapter->tx_ring;
2939 u64 tdba;
2940 u32 tdlen, tctl, tarc;
2941
2942 /* Setup the HW Tx Head and Tail descriptor pointers */
2943 tdba = tx_ring->dma;
2944 tdlen = tx_ring->count * sizeof(struct e1000_tx_desc);
2945 ew32(TDBAL(0), (tdba & DMA_BIT_MASK(32)));
2946 ew32(TDBAH(0), (tdba >> 32));
2947 ew32(TDLEN(0), tdlen);
2948 ew32(TDH(0), 0);
2949 ew32(TDT(0), 0);
2950 tx_ring->head = adapter->hw.hw_addr + E1000_TDH(0);
2951 tx_ring->tail = adapter->hw.hw_addr + E1000_TDT(0);
2952
2953 writel(0, tx_ring->head);
2954 if (adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_PCIM2PCI_ARBITER_WA)
2955 e1000e_update_tdt_wa(tx_ring, 0);
2956 else
2957 writel(0, tx_ring->tail);
2958
2959 /* Set the Tx Interrupt Delay register */
2960 ew32(TIDV, adapter->tx_int_delay);
2961 /* Tx irq moderation */
2962 ew32(TADV, adapter->tx_abs_int_delay);
2963
2964 if (adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_DMA_BURST) {
2965 u32 txdctl = er32(TXDCTL(0));
2966
2967 txdctl &= ~(E1000_TXDCTL_PTHRESH | E1000_TXDCTL_HTHRESH |
2968 E1000_TXDCTL_WTHRESH);
2969 /* set up some performance related parameters to encourage the
2970 * hardware to use the bus more efficiently in bursts, depends
2971 * on the tx_int_delay to be enabled,
2972 * wthresh = 1 ==> burst write is disabled to avoid Tx stalls
2973 * hthresh = 1 ==> prefetch when one or more available
2974 * pthresh = 0x1f ==> prefetch if internal cache 31 or less
2975 * BEWARE: this seems to work but should be considered first if
2976 * there are Tx hangs or other Tx related bugs
2977 */
2978 txdctl |= E1000_TXDCTL_DMA_BURST_ENABLE;
2979 ew32(TXDCTL(0), txdctl);
2980 }
2981 /* erratum work around: set txdctl the same for both queues */
2982 ew32(TXDCTL(1), er32(TXDCTL(0)));
2983
2984 /* Program the Transmit Control Register */
2985 tctl = er32(TCTL);
2986 tctl &= ~E1000_TCTL_CT;
2987 tctl |= E1000_TCTL_PSP | E1000_TCTL_RTLC |
2988 (E1000_COLLISION_THRESHOLD << E1000_CT_SHIFT);
2989
2990 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_TARC_SPEED_MODE_BIT) {
2991 tarc = er32(TARC(0));
2992 /* set the speed mode bit, we'll clear it if we're not at
2993 * gigabit link later
2994 */
2995#define SPEED_MODE_BIT BIT(21)
2996 tarc |= SPEED_MODE_BIT;
2997 ew32(TARC(0), tarc);
2998 }
2999
3000 /* errata: program both queues to unweighted RR */
3001 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_TARC_SET_BIT_ZERO) {
3002 tarc = er32(TARC(0));
3003 tarc |= 1;
3004 ew32(TARC(0), tarc);
3005 tarc = er32(TARC(1));
3006 tarc |= 1;
3007 ew32(TARC(1), tarc);
3008 }
3009
3010 /* Setup Transmit Descriptor Settings for eop descriptor */
3011 adapter->txd_cmd = E1000_TXD_CMD_EOP | E1000_TXD_CMD_IFCS;
3012
3013 /* only set IDE if we are delaying interrupts using the timers */
3014 if (adapter->tx_int_delay)
3015 adapter->txd_cmd |= E1000_TXD_CMD_IDE;
3016
3017 /* enable Report Status bit */
3018 adapter->txd_cmd |= E1000_TXD_CMD_RS;
3019
3020 ew32(TCTL, tctl);
3021
3022 hw->mac.ops.config_collision_dist(hw);
3023
3024 /* SPT and KBL Si errata workaround to avoid data corruption */
3025 if (hw->mac.type == e1000_pch_spt) {
3026 u32 reg_val;
3027
3028 reg_val = er32(IOSFPC);
3029 reg_val |= E1000_RCTL_RDMTS_HEX;
3030 ew32(IOSFPC, reg_val);
3031
3032 reg_val = er32(TARC(0));
3033 /* SPT and KBL Si errata workaround to avoid Tx hang.
3034 * Dropping the number of outstanding requests from
3035 * 3 to 2 in order to avoid a buffer overrun.
3036 */
3037 reg_val &= ~E1000_TARC0_CB_MULTIQ_3_REQ;
3038 reg_val |= E1000_TARC0_CB_MULTIQ_2_REQ;
3039 ew32(TARC(0), reg_val);
3040 }
3041}
3042
3043/**
3044 * e1000_setup_rctl - configure the receive control registers
3045 * @adapter: Board private structure
3046 **/
3047#define PAGE_USE_COUNT(S) (((S) >> PAGE_SHIFT) + \
3048 (((S) & (PAGE_SIZE - 1)) ? 1 : 0))
3049static void e1000_setup_rctl(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3050{
3051 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3052 u32 rctl, rfctl;
3053 u32 pages = 0;
3054
3055 /* Workaround Si errata on PCHx - configure jumbo frame flow.
3056 * If jumbo frames not set, program related MAC/PHY registers
3057 * to h/w defaults
3058 */
3059 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_pch2lan) {
3060 s32 ret_val;
3061
3062 if (adapter->netdev->mtu > ETH_DATA_LEN)
3063 ret_val = e1000_lv_jumbo_workaround_ich8lan(hw, true);
3064 else
3065 ret_val = e1000_lv_jumbo_workaround_ich8lan(hw, false);
3066
3067 if (ret_val)
3068 e_dbg("failed to enable|disable jumbo frame workaround mode\n");
3069 }
3070
3071 /* Program MC offset vector base */
3072 rctl = er32(RCTL);
3073 rctl &= ~(3 << E1000_RCTL_MO_SHIFT);
3074 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_EN | E1000_RCTL_BAM |
3075 E1000_RCTL_LBM_NO | E1000_RCTL_RDMTS_HALF |
3076 (adapter->hw.mac.mc_filter_type << E1000_RCTL_MO_SHIFT);
3077
3078 /* Do not Store bad packets */
3079 rctl &= ~E1000_RCTL_SBP;
3080
3081 /* Enable Long Packet receive */
3082 if (adapter->netdev->mtu <= ETH_DATA_LEN)
3083 rctl &= ~E1000_RCTL_LPE;
3084 else
3085 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_LPE;
3086
3087 /* Some systems expect that the CRC is included in SMBUS traffic. The
3088 * hardware strips the CRC before sending to both SMBUS (BMC) and to
3089 * host memory when this is enabled
3090 */
3091 if (adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_CRC_STRIPPING)
3092 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_SECRC;
3093
3094 /* Workaround Si errata on 82577 PHY - configure IPG for jumbos */
3095 if ((hw->phy.type == e1000_phy_82577) && (rctl & E1000_RCTL_LPE)) {
3096 u16 phy_data;
3097
3098 e1e_rphy(hw, PHY_REG(770, 26), &phy_data);
3099 phy_data &= 0xfff8;
3100 phy_data |= BIT(2);
3101 e1e_wphy(hw, PHY_REG(770, 26), phy_data);
3102
3103 e1e_rphy(hw, 22, &phy_data);
3104 phy_data &= 0x0fff;
3105 phy_data |= BIT(14);
3106 e1e_wphy(hw, 0x10, 0x2823);
3107 e1e_wphy(hw, 0x11, 0x0003);
3108 e1e_wphy(hw, 22, phy_data);
3109 }
3110
3111 /* Setup buffer sizes */
3112 rctl &= ~E1000_RCTL_SZ_4096;
3113 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_BSEX;
3114 switch (adapter->rx_buffer_len) {
3115 case 2048:
3116 default:
3117 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_SZ_2048;
3118 rctl &= ~E1000_RCTL_BSEX;
3119 break;
3120 case 4096:
3121 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_SZ_4096;
3122 break;
3123 case 8192:
3124 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_SZ_8192;
3125 break;
3126 case 16384:
3127 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_SZ_16384;
3128 break;
3129 }
3130
3131 /* Enable Extended Status in all Receive Descriptors */
3132 rfctl = er32(RFCTL);
3133 rfctl |= E1000_RFCTL_EXTEN;
3134 ew32(RFCTL, rfctl);
3135
3136 /* 82571 and greater support packet-split where the protocol
3137 * header is placed in skb->data and the packet data is
3138 * placed in pages hanging off of skb_shinfo(skb)->nr_frags.
3139 * In the case of a non-split, skb->data is linearly filled,
3140 * followed by the page buffers. Therefore, skb->data is
3141 * sized to hold the largest protocol header.
3142 *
3143 * allocations using alloc_page take too long for regular MTU
3144 * so only enable packet split for jumbo frames
3145 *
3146 * Using pages when the page size is greater than 16k wastes
3147 * a lot of memory, since we allocate 3 pages at all times
3148 * per packet.
3149 */
3150 pages = PAGE_USE_COUNT(adapter->netdev->mtu);
3151 if ((pages <= 3) && (PAGE_SIZE <= 16384) && (rctl & E1000_RCTL_LPE))
3152 adapter->rx_ps_pages = pages;
3153 else
3154 adapter->rx_ps_pages = 0;
3155
3156 if (adapter->rx_ps_pages) {
3157 u32 psrctl = 0;
3158
3159 /* Enable Packet split descriptors */
3160 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_DTYP_PS;
3161
3162 psrctl |= adapter->rx_ps_bsize0 >> E1000_PSRCTL_BSIZE0_SHIFT;
3163
3164 switch (adapter->rx_ps_pages) {
3165 case 3:
3166 psrctl |= PAGE_SIZE << E1000_PSRCTL_BSIZE3_SHIFT;
3167 /* fall-through */
3168 case 2:
3169 psrctl |= PAGE_SIZE << E1000_PSRCTL_BSIZE2_SHIFT;
3170 /* fall-through */
3171 case 1:
3172 psrctl |= PAGE_SIZE >> E1000_PSRCTL_BSIZE1_SHIFT;
3173 break;
3174 }
3175
3176 ew32(PSRCTL, psrctl);
3177 }
3178
3179 /* This is useful for sniffing bad packets. */
3180 if (adapter->netdev->features & NETIF_F_RXALL) {
3181 /* UPE and MPE will be handled by normal PROMISC logic
3182 * in e1000e_set_rx_mode
3183 */
3184 rctl |= (E1000_RCTL_SBP | /* Receive bad packets */
3185 E1000_RCTL_BAM | /* RX All Bcast Pkts */
3186 E1000_RCTL_PMCF); /* RX All MAC Ctrl Pkts */
3187
3188 rctl &= ~(E1000_RCTL_VFE | /* Disable VLAN filter */
3189 E1000_RCTL_DPF | /* Allow filtered pause */
3190 E1000_RCTL_CFIEN); /* Dis VLAN CFIEN Filter */
3191 /* Do not mess with E1000_CTRL_VME, it affects transmit as well,
3192 * and that breaks VLANs.
3193 */
3194 }
3195
3196 ew32(RCTL, rctl);
3197 /* just started the receive unit, no need to restart */
3198 adapter->flags &= ~FLAG_RESTART_NOW;
3199}
3200
3201/**
3202 * e1000_configure_rx - Configure Receive Unit after Reset
3203 * @adapter: board private structure
3204 *
3205 * Configure the Rx unit of the MAC after a reset.
3206 **/
3207static void e1000_configure_rx(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3208{
3209 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3210 struct e1000_ring *rx_ring = adapter->rx_ring;
3211 u64 rdba;
3212 u32 rdlen, rctl, rxcsum, ctrl_ext;
3213
3214 if (adapter->rx_ps_pages) {
3215 /* this is a 32 byte descriptor */
3216 rdlen = rx_ring->count *
3217 sizeof(union e1000_rx_desc_packet_split);
3218 adapter->clean_rx = e1000_clean_rx_irq_ps;
3219 adapter->alloc_rx_buf = e1000_alloc_rx_buffers_ps;
3220 } else if (adapter->netdev->mtu > ETH_FRAME_LEN + ETH_FCS_LEN) {
3221 rdlen = rx_ring->count * sizeof(union e1000_rx_desc_extended);
3222 adapter->clean_rx = e1000_clean_jumbo_rx_irq;
3223 adapter->alloc_rx_buf = e1000_alloc_jumbo_rx_buffers;
3224 } else {
3225 rdlen = rx_ring->count * sizeof(union e1000_rx_desc_extended);
3226 adapter->clean_rx = e1000_clean_rx_irq;
3227 adapter->alloc_rx_buf = e1000_alloc_rx_buffers;
3228 }
3229
3230 /* disable receives while setting up the descriptors */
3231 rctl = er32(RCTL);
3232 if (!(adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_NO_DISABLE_RX))
3233 ew32(RCTL, rctl & ~E1000_RCTL_EN);
3234 e1e_flush();
3235 usleep_range(10000, 20000);
3236
3237 if (adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_DMA_BURST) {
3238 /* set the writeback threshold (only takes effect if the RDTR
3239 * is set). set GRAN=1 and write back up to 0x4 worth, and
3240 * enable prefetching of 0x20 Rx descriptors
3241 * granularity = 01
3242 * wthresh = 04,
3243 * hthresh = 04,
3244 * pthresh = 0x20
3245 */
3246 ew32(RXDCTL(0), E1000_RXDCTL_DMA_BURST_ENABLE);
3247 ew32(RXDCTL(1), E1000_RXDCTL_DMA_BURST_ENABLE);
3248
3249 /* override the delay timers for enabling bursting, only if
3250 * the value was not set by the user via module options
3251 */
3252 if (adapter->rx_int_delay == DEFAULT_RDTR)
3253 adapter->rx_int_delay = BURST_RDTR;
3254 if (adapter->rx_abs_int_delay == DEFAULT_RADV)
3255 adapter->rx_abs_int_delay = BURST_RADV;
3256 }
3257
3258 /* set the Receive Delay Timer Register */
3259 ew32(RDTR, adapter->rx_int_delay);
3260
3261 /* irq moderation */
3262 ew32(RADV, adapter->rx_abs_int_delay);
3263 if ((adapter->itr_setting != 0) && (adapter->itr != 0))
3264 e1000e_write_itr(adapter, adapter->itr);
3265
3266 ctrl_ext = er32(CTRL_EXT);
3267 /* Auto-Mask interrupts upon ICR access */
3268 ctrl_ext |= E1000_CTRL_EXT_IAME;
3269 ew32(IAM, 0xffffffff);
3270 ew32(CTRL_EXT, ctrl_ext);
3271 e1e_flush();
3272
3273 /* Setup the HW Rx Head and Tail Descriptor Pointers and
3274 * the Base and Length of the Rx Descriptor Ring
3275 */
3276 rdba = rx_ring->dma;
3277 ew32(RDBAL(0), (rdba & DMA_BIT_MASK(32)));
3278 ew32(RDBAH(0), (rdba >> 32));
3279 ew32(RDLEN(0), rdlen);
3280 ew32(RDH(0), 0);
3281 ew32(RDT(0), 0);
3282 rx_ring->head = adapter->hw.hw_addr + E1000_RDH(0);
3283 rx_ring->tail = adapter->hw.hw_addr + E1000_RDT(0);
3284
3285 writel(0, rx_ring->head);
3286 if (adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_PCIM2PCI_ARBITER_WA)
3287 e1000e_update_rdt_wa(rx_ring, 0);
3288 else
3289 writel(0, rx_ring->tail);
3290
3291 /* Enable Receive Checksum Offload for TCP and UDP */
3292 rxcsum = er32(RXCSUM);
3293 if (adapter->netdev->features & NETIF_F_RXCSUM)
3294 rxcsum |= E1000_RXCSUM_TUOFL;
3295 else
3296 rxcsum &= ~E1000_RXCSUM_TUOFL;
3297 ew32(RXCSUM, rxcsum);
3298
3299 /* With jumbo frames, excessive C-state transition latencies result
3300 * in dropped transactions.
3301 */
3302 if (adapter->netdev->mtu > ETH_DATA_LEN) {
3303 u32 lat =
3304 ((er32(PBA) & E1000_PBA_RXA_MASK) * 1024 -
3305 adapter->max_frame_size) * 8 / 1000;
3306
3307 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_IS_ICH) {
3308 u32 rxdctl = er32(RXDCTL(0));
3309
3310 ew32(RXDCTL(0), rxdctl | 0x3);
3311 }
3312
3313 pm_qos_update_request(&adapter->pm_qos_req, lat);
3314 } else {
3315 pm_qos_update_request(&adapter->pm_qos_req,
3316 PM_QOS_DEFAULT_VALUE);
3317 }
3318
3319 /* Enable Receives */
3320 ew32(RCTL, rctl);
3321}
3322
3323/**
3324 * e1000e_write_mc_addr_list - write multicast addresses to MTA
3325 * @netdev: network interface device structure
3326 *
3327 * Writes multicast address list to the MTA hash table.
3328 * Returns: -ENOMEM on failure
3329 * 0 on no addresses written
3330 * X on writing X addresses to MTA
3331 */
3332static int e1000e_write_mc_addr_list(struct net_device *netdev)
3333{
3334 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
3335 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3336 struct netdev_hw_addr *ha;
3337 u8 *mta_list;
3338 int i;
3339
3340 if (netdev_mc_empty(netdev)) {
3341 /* nothing to program, so clear mc list */
3342 hw->mac.ops.update_mc_addr_list(hw, NULL, 0);
3343 return 0;
3344 }
3345
3346 mta_list = kzalloc(netdev_mc_count(netdev) * ETH_ALEN, GFP_ATOMIC);
3347 if (!mta_list)
3348 return -ENOMEM;
3349
3350 /* update_mc_addr_list expects a packed array of only addresses. */
3351 i = 0;
3352 netdev_for_each_mc_addr(ha, netdev)
3353 memcpy(mta_list + (i++ * ETH_ALEN), ha->addr, ETH_ALEN);
3354
3355 hw->mac.ops.update_mc_addr_list(hw, mta_list, i);
3356 kfree(mta_list);
3357
3358 return netdev_mc_count(netdev);
3359}
3360
3361/**
3362 * e1000e_write_uc_addr_list - write unicast addresses to RAR table
3363 * @netdev: network interface device structure
3364 *
3365 * Writes unicast address list to the RAR table.
3366 * Returns: -ENOMEM on failure/insufficient address space
3367 * 0 on no addresses written
3368 * X on writing X addresses to the RAR table
3369 **/
3370static int e1000e_write_uc_addr_list(struct net_device *netdev)
3371{
3372 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
3373 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3374 unsigned int rar_entries;
3375 int count = 0;
3376
3377 rar_entries = hw->mac.ops.rar_get_count(hw);
3378
3379 /* save a rar entry for our hardware address */
3380 rar_entries--;
3381
3382 /* save a rar entry for the LAA workaround */
3383 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_RESET_OVERWRITES_LAA)
3384 rar_entries--;
3385
3386 /* return ENOMEM indicating insufficient memory for addresses */
3387 if (netdev_uc_count(netdev) > rar_entries)
3388 return -ENOMEM;
3389
3390 if (!netdev_uc_empty(netdev) && rar_entries) {
3391 struct netdev_hw_addr *ha;
3392
3393 /* write the addresses in reverse order to avoid write
3394 * combining
3395 */
3396 netdev_for_each_uc_addr(ha, netdev) {
3397 int ret_val;
3398
3399 if (!rar_entries)
3400 break;
3401 ret_val = hw->mac.ops.rar_set(hw, ha->addr, rar_entries--);
3402 if (ret_val < 0)
3403 return -ENOMEM;
3404 count++;
3405 }
3406 }
3407
3408 /* zero out the remaining RAR entries not used above */
3409 for (; rar_entries > 0; rar_entries--) {
3410 ew32(RAH(rar_entries), 0);
3411 ew32(RAL(rar_entries), 0);
3412 }
3413 e1e_flush();
3414
3415 return count;
3416}
3417
3418/**
3419 * e1000e_set_rx_mode - secondary unicast, Multicast and Promiscuous mode set
3420 * @netdev: network interface device structure
3421 *
3422 * The ndo_set_rx_mode entry point is called whenever the unicast or multicast
3423 * address list or the network interface flags are updated. This routine is
3424 * responsible for configuring the hardware for proper unicast, multicast,
3425 * promiscuous mode, and all-multi behavior.
3426 **/
3427static void e1000e_set_rx_mode(struct net_device *netdev)
3428{
3429 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
3430 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3431 u32 rctl;
3432
3433 if (pm_runtime_suspended(netdev->dev.parent))
3434 return;
3435
3436 /* Check for Promiscuous and All Multicast modes */
3437 rctl = er32(RCTL);
3438
3439 /* clear the affected bits */
3440 rctl &= ~(E1000_RCTL_UPE | E1000_RCTL_MPE);
3441
3442 if (netdev->flags & IFF_PROMISC) {
3443 rctl |= (E1000_RCTL_UPE | E1000_RCTL_MPE);
3444 /* Do not hardware filter VLANs in promisc mode */
3445 e1000e_vlan_filter_disable(adapter);
3446 } else {
3447 int count;
3448
3449 if (netdev->flags & IFF_ALLMULTI) {
3450 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_MPE;
3451 } else {
3452 /* Write addresses to the MTA, if the attempt fails
3453 * then we should just turn on promiscuous mode so
3454 * that we can at least receive multicast traffic
3455 */
3456 count = e1000e_write_mc_addr_list(netdev);
3457 if (count < 0)
3458 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_MPE;
3459 }
3460 e1000e_vlan_filter_enable(adapter);
3461 /* Write addresses to available RAR registers, if there is not
3462 * sufficient space to store all the addresses then enable
3463 * unicast promiscuous mode
3464 */
3465 count = e1000e_write_uc_addr_list(netdev);
3466 if (count < 0)
3467 rctl |= E1000_RCTL_UPE;
3468 }
3469
3470 ew32(RCTL, rctl);
3471
3472 if (netdev->features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX)
3473 e1000e_vlan_strip_enable(adapter);
3474 else
3475 e1000e_vlan_strip_disable(adapter);
3476}
3477
3478static void e1000e_setup_rss_hash(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3479{
3480 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3481 u32 mrqc, rxcsum;
3482 u32 rss_key[10];
3483 int i;
3484
3485 netdev_rss_key_fill(rss_key, sizeof(rss_key));
3486 for (i = 0; i < 10; i++)
3487 ew32(RSSRK(i), rss_key[i]);
3488
3489 /* Direct all traffic to queue 0 */
3490 for (i = 0; i < 32; i++)
3491 ew32(RETA(i), 0);
3492
3493 /* Disable raw packet checksumming so that RSS hash is placed in
3494 * descriptor on writeback.
3495 */
3496 rxcsum = er32(RXCSUM);
3497 rxcsum |= E1000_RXCSUM_PCSD;
3498
3499 ew32(RXCSUM, rxcsum);
3500
3501 mrqc = (E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV4 |
3502 E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV4_TCP |
3503 E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6 |
3504 E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6_TCP |
3505 E1000_MRQC_RSS_FIELD_IPV6_TCP_EX);
3506
3507 ew32(MRQC, mrqc);
3508}
3509
3510/**
3511 * e1000e_get_base_timinca - get default SYSTIM time increment attributes
3512 * @adapter: board private structure
3513 * @timinca: pointer to returned time increment attributes
3514 *
3515 * Get attributes for incrementing the System Time Register SYSTIML/H at
3516 * the default base frequency, and set the cyclecounter shift value.
3517 **/
3518s32 e1000e_get_base_timinca(struct e1000_adapter *adapter, u32 *timinca)
3519{
3520 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3521 u32 incvalue, incperiod, shift;
3522
3523 /* Make sure clock is enabled on I217/I218/I219 before checking
3524 * the frequency
3525 */
3526 if ((hw->mac.type >= e1000_pch_lpt) &&
3527 !(er32(TSYNCTXCTL) & E1000_TSYNCTXCTL_ENABLED) &&
3528 !(er32(TSYNCRXCTL) & E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_ENABLED)) {
3529 u32 fextnvm7 = er32(FEXTNVM7);
3530
3531 if (!(fextnvm7 & BIT(0))) {
3532 ew32(FEXTNVM7, fextnvm7 | BIT(0));
3533 e1e_flush();
3534 }
3535 }
3536
3537 switch (hw->mac.type) {
3538 case e1000_pch2lan:
3539 /* Stable 96MHz frequency */
3540 incperiod = INCPERIOD_96MHZ;
3541 incvalue = INCVALUE_96MHZ;
3542 shift = INCVALUE_SHIFT_96MHZ;
3543 adapter->cc.shift = shift + INCPERIOD_SHIFT_96MHZ;
3544 break;
3545 case e1000_pch_lpt:
3546 if (er32(TSYNCRXCTL) & E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_SYSCFI) {
3547 /* Stable 96MHz frequency */
3548 incperiod = INCPERIOD_96MHZ;
3549 incvalue = INCVALUE_96MHZ;
3550 shift = INCVALUE_SHIFT_96MHZ;
3551 adapter->cc.shift = shift + INCPERIOD_SHIFT_96MHZ;
3552 } else {
3553 /* Stable 25MHz frequency */
3554 incperiod = INCPERIOD_25MHZ;
3555 incvalue = INCVALUE_25MHZ;
3556 shift = INCVALUE_SHIFT_25MHZ;
3557 adapter->cc.shift = shift;
3558 }
3559 break;
3560 case e1000_pch_spt:
3561 if (er32(TSYNCRXCTL) & E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_SYSCFI) {
3562 /* Stable 24MHz frequency */
3563 incperiod = INCPERIOD_24MHZ;
3564 incvalue = INCVALUE_24MHZ;
3565 shift = INCVALUE_SHIFT_24MHZ;
3566 adapter->cc.shift = shift;
3567 break;
3568 }
3569 return -EINVAL;
3570 case e1000_pch_cnp:
3571 if (er32(TSYNCRXCTL) & E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_SYSCFI) {
3572 /* Stable 24MHz frequency */
3573 incperiod = INCPERIOD_24MHZ;
3574 incvalue = INCVALUE_24MHZ;
3575 shift = INCVALUE_SHIFT_24MHZ;
3576 adapter->cc.shift = shift;
3577 } else {
3578 /* Stable 38400KHz frequency */
3579 incperiod = INCPERIOD_38400KHZ;
3580 incvalue = INCVALUE_38400KHZ;
3581 shift = INCVALUE_SHIFT_38400KHZ;
3582 adapter->cc.shift = shift;
3583 }
3584 break;
3585 case e1000_82574:
3586 case e1000_82583:
3587 /* Stable 25MHz frequency */
3588 incperiod = INCPERIOD_25MHZ;
3589 incvalue = INCVALUE_25MHZ;
3590 shift = INCVALUE_SHIFT_25MHZ;
3591 adapter->cc.shift = shift;
3592 break;
3593 default:
3594 return -EINVAL;
3595 }
3596
3597 *timinca = ((incperiod << E1000_TIMINCA_INCPERIOD_SHIFT) |
3598 ((incvalue << shift) & E1000_TIMINCA_INCVALUE_MASK));
3599
3600 return 0;
3601}
3602
3603/**
3604 * e1000e_config_hwtstamp - configure the hwtstamp registers and enable/disable
3605 * @adapter: board private structure
3606 *
3607 * Outgoing time stamping can be enabled and disabled. Play nice and
3608 * disable it when requested, although it shouldn't cause any overhead
3609 * when no packet needs it. At most one packet in the queue may be
3610 * marked for time stamping, otherwise it would be impossible to tell
3611 * for sure to which packet the hardware time stamp belongs.
3612 *
3613 * Incoming time stamping has to be configured via the hardware filters.
3614 * Not all combinations are supported, in particular event type has to be
3615 * specified. Matching the kind of event packet is not supported, with the
3616 * exception of "all V2 events regardless of level 2 or 4".
3617 **/
3618static int e1000e_config_hwtstamp(struct e1000_adapter *adapter,
3619 struct hwtstamp_config *config)
3620{
3621 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3622 u32 tsync_tx_ctl = E1000_TSYNCTXCTL_ENABLED;
3623 u32 tsync_rx_ctl = E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_ENABLED;
3624 u32 rxmtrl = 0;
3625 u16 rxudp = 0;
3626 bool is_l4 = false;
3627 bool is_l2 = false;
3628 u32 regval;
3629
3630 if (!(adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_HW_TIMESTAMP))
3631 return -EINVAL;
3632
3633 /* flags reserved for future extensions - must be zero */
3634 if (config->flags)
3635 return -EINVAL;
3636
3637 switch (config->tx_type) {
3638 case HWTSTAMP_TX_OFF:
3639 tsync_tx_ctl = 0;
3640 break;
3641 case HWTSTAMP_TX_ON:
3642 break;
3643 default:
3644 return -ERANGE;
3645 }
3646
3647 switch (config->rx_filter) {
3648 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_NONE:
3649 tsync_rx_ctl = 0;
3650 break;
3651 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V1_L4_SYNC:
3652 tsync_rx_ctl |= E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_L4_V1;
3653 rxmtrl = E1000_RXMTRL_PTP_V1_SYNC_MESSAGE;
3654 is_l4 = true;
3655 break;
3656 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V1_L4_DELAY_REQ:
3657 tsync_rx_ctl |= E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_L4_V1;
3658 rxmtrl = E1000_RXMTRL_PTP_V1_DELAY_REQ_MESSAGE;
3659 is_l4 = true;
3660 break;
3661 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_L2_SYNC:
3662 /* Also time stamps V2 L2 Path Delay Request/Response */
3663 tsync_rx_ctl |= E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_L2_V2;
3664 rxmtrl = E1000_RXMTRL_PTP_V2_SYNC_MESSAGE;
3665 is_l2 = true;
3666 break;
3667 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_L2_DELAY_REQ:
3668 /* Also time stamps V2 L2 Path Delay Request/Response. */
3669 tsync_rx_ctl |= E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_L2_V2;
3670 rxmtrl = E1000_RXMTRL_PTP_V2_DELAY_REQ_MESSAGE;
3671 is_l2 = true;
3672 break;
3673 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_L4_SYNC:
3674 /* Hardware cannot filter just V2 L4 Sync messages;
3675 * fall-through to V2 (both L2 and L4) Sync.
3676 */
3677 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_SYNC:
3678 /* Also time stamps V2 Path Delay Request/Response. */
3679 tsync_rx_ctl |= E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_L2_L4_V2;
3680 rxmtrl = E1000_RXMTRL_PTP_V2_SYNC_MESSAGE;
3681 is_l2 = true;
3682 is_l4 = true;
3683 break;
3684 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_L4_DELAY_REQ:
3685 /* Hardware cannot filter just V2 L4 Delay Request messages;
3686 * fall-through to V2 (both L2 and L4) Delay Request.
3687 */
3688 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_DELAY_REQ:
3689 /* Also time stamps V2 Path Delay Request/Response. */
3690 tsync_rx_ctl |= E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_L2_L4_V2;
3691 rxmtrl = E1000_RXMTRL_PTP_V2_DELAY_REQ_MESSAGE;
3692 is_l2 = true;
3693 is_l4 = true;
3694 break;
3695 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_L4_EVENT:
3696 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_L2_EVENT:
3697 /* Hardware cannot filter just V2 L4 or L2 Event messages;
3698 * fall-through to all V2 (both L2 and L4) Events.
3699 */
3700 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_EVENT:
3701 tsync_rx_ctl |= E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_EVENT_V2;
3702 config->rx_filter = HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V2_EVENT;
3703 is_l2 = true;
3704 is_l4 = true;
3705 break;
3706 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_PTP_V1_L4_EVENT:
3707 /* For V1, the hardware can only filter Sync messages or
3708 * Delay Request messages but not both so fall-through to
3709 * time stamp all packets.
3710 */
3711 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_NTP_ALL:
3712 case HWTSTAMP_FILTER_ALL:
3713 is_l2 = true;
3714 is_l4 = true;
3715 tsync_rx_ctl |= E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_ALL;
3716 config->rx_filter = HWTSTAMP_FILTER_ALL;
3717 break;
3718 default:
3719 return -ERANGE;
3720 }
3721
3722 adapter->hwtstamp_config = *config;
3723
3724 /* enable/disable Tx h/w time stamping */
3725 regval = er32(TSYNCTXCTL);
3726 regval &= ~E1000_TSYNCTXCTL_ENABLED;
3727 regval |= tsync_tx_ctl;
3728 ew32(TSYNCTXCTL, regval);
3729 if ((er32(TSYNCTXCTL) & E1000_TSYNCTXCTL_ENABLED) !=
3730 (regval & E1000_TSYNCTXCTL_ENABLED)) {
3731 e_err("Timesync Tx Control register not set as expected\n");
3732 return -EAGAIN;
3733 }
3734
3735 /* enable/disable Rx h/w time stamping */
3736 regval = er32(TSYNCRXCTL);
3737 regval &= ~(E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_ENABLED | E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_MASK);
3738 regval |= tsync_rx_ctl;
3739 ew32(TSYNCRXCTL, regval);
3740 if ((er32(TSYNCRXCTL) & (E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_ENABLED |
3741 E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_MASK)) !=
3742 (regval & (E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_ENABLED |
3743 E1000_TSYNCRXCTL_TYPE_MASK))) {
3744 e_err("Timesync Rx Control register not set as expected\n");
3745 return -EAGAIN;
3746 }
3747
3748 /* L2: define ethertype filter for time stamped packets */
3749 if (is_l2)
3750 rxmtrl |= ETH_P_1588;
3751
3752 /* define which PTP packets get time stamped */
3753 ew32(RXMTRL, rxmtrl);
3754
3755 /* Filter by destination port */
3756 if (is_l4) {
3757 rxudp = PTP_EV_PORT;
3758 cpu_to_be16s(&rxudp);
3759 }
3760 ew32(RXUDP, rxudp);
3761
3762 e1e_flush();
3763
3764 /* Clear TSYNCRXCTL_VALID & TSYNCTXCTL_VALID bit */
3765 er32(RXSTMPH);
3766 er32(TXSTMPH);
3767
3768 return 0;
3769}
3770
3771/**
3772 * e1000_configure - configure the hardware for Rx and Tx
3773 * @adapter: private board structure
3774 **/
3775static void e1000_configure(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3776{
3777 struct e1000_ring *rx_ring = adapter->rx_ring;
3778
3779 e1000e_set_rx_mode(adapter->netdev);
3780
3781 e1000_restore_vlan(adapter);
3782 e1000_init_manageability_pt(adapter);
3783
3784 e1000_configure_tx(adapter);
3785
3786 if (adapter->netdev->features & NETIF_F_RXHASH)
3787 e1000e_setup_rss_hash(adapter);
3788 e1000_setup_rctl(adapter);
3789 e1000_configure_rx(adapter);
3790 adapter->alloc_rx_buf(rx_ring, e1000_desc_unused(rx_ring), GFP_KERNEL);
3791}
3792
3793/**
3794 * e1000e_power_up_phy - restore link in case the phy was powered down
3795 * @adapter: address of board private structure
3796 *
3797 * The phy may be powered down to save power and turn off link when the
3798 * driver is unloaded and wake on lan is not enabled (among others)
3799 * *** this routine MUST be followed by a call to e1000e_reset ***
3800 **/
3801void e1000e_power_up_phy(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3802{
3803 if (adapter->hw.phy.ops.power_up)
3804 adapter->hw.phy.ops.power_up(&adapter->hw);
3805
3806 adapter->hw.mac.ops.setup_link(&adapter->hw);
3807}
3808
3809/**
3810 * e1000_power_down_phy - Power down the PHY
3811 *
3812 * Power down the PHY so no link is implied when interface is down.
3813 * The PHY cannot be powered down if management or WoL is active.
3814 */
3815static void e1000_power_down_phy(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3816{
3817 if (adapter->hw.phy.ops.power_down)
3818 adapter->hw.phy.ops.power_down(&adapter->hw);
3819}
3820
3821/**
3822 * e1000_flush_tx_ring - remove all descriptors from the tx_ring
3823 *
3824 * We want to clear all pending descriptors from the TX ring.
3825 * zeroing happens when the HW reads the regs. We assign the ring itself as
3826 * the data of the next descriptor. We don't care about the data we are about
3827 * to reset the HW.
3828 */
3829static void e1000_flush_tx_ring(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3830{
3831 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3832 struct e1000_ring *tx_ring = adapter->tx_ring;
3833 struct e1000_tx_desc *tx_desc = NULL;
3834 u32 tdt, tctl, txd_lower = E1000_TXD_CMD_IFCS;
3835 u16 size = 512;
3836
3837 tctl = er32(TCTL);
3838 ew32(TCTL, tctl | E1000_TCTL_EN);
3839 tdt = er32(TDT(0));
3840 BUG_ON(tdt != tx_ring->next_to_use);
3841 tx_desc = E1000_TX_DESC(*tx_ring, tx_ring->next_to_use);
3842 tx_desc->buffer_addr = tx_ring->dma;
3843
3844 tx_desc->lower.data = cpu_to_le32(txd_lower | size);
3845 tx_desc->upper.data = 0;
3846 /* flush descriptors to memory before notifying the HW */
3847 wmb();
3848 tx_ring->next_to_use++;
3849 if (tx_ring->next_to_use == tx_ring->count)
3850 tx_ring->next_to_use = 0;
3851 ew32(TDT(0), tx_ring->next_to_use);
3852 mmiowb();
3853 usleep_range(200, 250);
3854}
3855
3856/**
3857 * e1000_flush_rx_ring - remove all descriptors from the rx_ring
3858 *
3859 * Mark all descriptors in the RX ring as consumed and disable the rx ring
3860 */
3861static void e1000_flush_rx_ring(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3862{
3863 u32 rctl, rxdctl;
3864 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3865
3866 rctl = er32(RCTL);
3867 ew32(RCTL, rctl & ~E1000_RCTL_EN);
3868 e1e_flush();
3869 usleep_range(100, 150);
3870
3871 rxdctl = er32(RXDCTL(0));
3872 /* zero the lower 14 bits (prefetch and host thresholds) */
3873 rxdctl &= 0xffffc000;
3874
3875 /* update thresholds: prefetch threshold to 31, host threshold to 1
3876 * and make sure the granularity is "descriptors" and not "cache lines"
3877 */
3878 rxdctl |= (0x1F | BIT(8) | E1000_RXDCTL_THRESH_UNIT_DESC);
3879
3880 ew32(RXDCTL(0), rxdctl);
3881 /* momentarily enable the RX ring for the changes to take effect */
3882 ew32(RCTL, rctl | E1000_RCTL_EN);
3883 e1e_flush();
3884 usleep_range(100, 150);
3885 ew32(RCTL, rctl & ~E1000_RCTL_EN);
3886}
3887
3888/**
3889 * e1000_flush_desc_rings - remove all descriptors from the descriptor rings
3890 *
3891 * In i219, the descriptor rings must be emptied before resetting the HW
3892 * or before changing the device state to D3 during runtime (runtime PM).
3893 *
3894 * Failure to do this will cause the HW to enter a unit hang state which can
3895 * only be released by PCI reset on the device
3896 *
3897 */
3898
3899static void e1000_flush_desc_rings(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3900{
3901 u16 hang_state;
3902 u32 fext_nvm11, tdlen;
3903 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3904
3905 /* First, disable MULR fix in FEXTNVM11 */
3906 fext_nvm11 = er32(FEXTNVM11);
3907 fext_nvm11 |= E1000_FEXTNVM11_DISABLE_MULR_FIX;
3908 ew32(FEXTNVM11, fext_nvm11);
3909 /* do nothing if we're not in faulty state, or if the queue is empty */
3910 tdlen = er32(TDLEN(0));
3911 pci_read_config_word(adapter->pdev, PCICFG_DESC_RING_STATUS,
3912 &hang_state);
3913 if (!(hang_state & FLUSH_DESC_REQUIRED) || !tdlen)
3914 return;
3915 e1000_flush_tx_ring(adapter);
3916 /* recheck, maybe the fault is caused by the rx ring */
3917 pci_read_config_word(adapter->pdev, PCICFG_DESC_RING_STATUS,
3918 &hang_state);
3919 if (hang_state & FLUSH_DESC_REQUIRED)
3920 e1000_flush_rx_ring(adapter);
3921}
3922
3923/**
3924 * e1000e_systim_reset - reset the timesync registers after a hardware reset
3925 * @adapter: board private structure
3926 *
3927 * When the MAC is reset, all hardware bits for timesync will be reset to the
3928 * default values. This function will restore the settings last in place.
3929 * Since the clock SYSTIME registers are reset, we will simply restore the
3930 * cyclecounter to the kernel real clock time.
3931 **/
3932static void e1000e_systim_reset(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3933{
3934 struct ptp_clock_info *info = &adapter->ptp_clock_info;
3935 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3936 unsigned long flags;
3937 u32 timinca;
3938 s32 ret_val;
3939
3940 if (!(adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_HW_TIMESTAMP))
3941 return;
3942
3943 if (info->adjfreq) {
3944 /* restore the previous ptp frequency delta */
3945 ret_val = info->adjfreq(info, adapter->ptp_delta);
3946 } else {
3947 /* set the default base frequency if no adjustment possible */
3948 ret_val = e1000e_get_base_timinca(adapter, &timinca);
3949 if (!ret_val)
3950 ew32(TIMINCA, timinca);
3951 }
3952
3953 if (ret_val) {
3954 dev_warn(&adapter->pdev->dev,
3955 "Failed to restore TIMINCA clock rate delta: %d\n",
3956 ret_val);
3957 return;
3958 }
3959
3960 /* reset the systim ns time counter */
3961 spin_lock_irqsave(&adapter->systim_lock, flags);
3962 timecounter_init(&adapter->tc, &adapter->cc,
3963 ktime_to_ns(ktime_get_real()));
3964 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&adapter->systim_lock, flags);
3965
3966 /* restore the previous hwtstamp configuration settings */
3967 e1000e_config_hwtstamp(adapter, &adapter->hwtstamp_config);
3968}
3969
3970/**
3971 * e1000e_reset - bring the hardware into a known good state
3972 *
3973 * This function boots the hardware and enables some settings that
3974 * require a configuration cycle of the hardware - those cannot be
3975 * set/changed during runtime. After reset the device needs to be
3976 * properly configured for Rx, Tx etc.
3977 */
3978void e1000e_reset(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
3979{
3980 struct e1000_mac_info *mac = &adapter->hw.mac;
3981 struct e1000_fc_info *fc = &adapter->hw.fc;
3982 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
3983 u32 tx_space, min_tx_space, min_rx_space;
3984 u32 pba = adapter->pba;
3985 u16 hwm;
3986
3987 /* reset Packet Buffer Allocation to default */
3988 ew32(PBA, pba);
3989
3990 if (adapter->max_frame_size > (VLAN_ETH_FRAME_LEN + ETH_FCS_LEN)) {
3991 /* To maintain wire speed transmits, the Tx FIFO should be
3992 * large enough to accommodate two full transmit packets,
3993 * rounded up to the next 1KB and expressed in KB. Likewise,
3994 * the Rx FIFO should be large enough to accommodate at least
3995 * one full receive packet and is similarly rounded up and
3996 * expressed in KB.
3997 */
3998 pba = er32(PBA);
3999 /* upper 16 bits has Tx packet buffer allocation size in KB */
4000 tx_space = pba >> 16;
4001 /* lower 16 bits has Rx packet buffer allocation size in KB */
4002 pba &= 0xffff;
4003 /* the Tx fifo also stores 16 bytes of information about the Tx
4004 * but don't include ethernet FCS because hardware appends it
4005 */
4006 min_tx_space = (adapter->max_frame_size +
4007 sizeof(struct e1000_tx_desc) - ETH_FCS_LEN) * 2;
4008 min_tx_space = ALIGN(min_tx_space, 1024);
4009 min_tx_space >>= 10;
4010 /* software strips receive CRC, so leave room for it */
4011 min_rx_space = adapter->max_frame_size;
4012 min_rx_space = ALIGN(min_rx_space, 1024);
4013 min_rx_space >>= 10;
4014
4015 /* If current Tx allocation is less than the min Tx FIFO size,
4016 * and the min Tx FIFO size is less than the current Rx FIFO
4017 * allocation, take space away from current Rx allocation
4018 */
4019 if ((tx_space < min_tx_space) &&
4020 ((min_tx_space - tx_space) < pba)) {
4021 pba -= min_tx_space - tx_space;
4022
4023 /* if short on Rx space, Rx wins and must trump Tx
4024 * adjustment
4025 */
4026 if (pba < min_rx_space)
4027 pba = min_rx_space;
4028 }
4029
4030 ew32(PBA, pba);
4031 }
4032
4033 /* flow control settings
4034 *
4035 * The high water mark must be low enough to fit one full frame
4036 * (or the size used for early receive) above it in the Rx FIFO.
4037 * Set it to the lower of:
4038 * - 90% of the Rx FIFO size, and
4039 * - the full Rx FIFO size minus one full frame
4040 */
4041 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_DISABLE_FC_PAUSE_TIME)
4042 fc->pause_time = 0xFFFF;
4043 else
4044 fc->pause_time = E1000_FC_PAUSE_TIME;
4045 fc->send_xon = true;
4046 fc->current_mode = fc->requested_mode;
4047
4048 switch (hw->mac.type) {
4049 case e1000_ich9lan:
4050 case e1000_ich10lan:
4051 if (adapter->netdev->mtu > ETH_DATA_LEN) {
4052 pba = 14;
4053 ew32(PBA, pba);
4054 fc->high_water = 0x2800;
4055 fc->low_water = fc->high_water - 8;
4056 break;
4057 }
4058 /* fall-through */
4059 default:
4060 hwm = min(((pba << 10) * 9 / 10),
4061 ((pba << 10) - adapter->max_frame_size));
4062
4063 fc->high_water = hwm & E1000_FCRTH_RTH; /* 8-byte granularity */
4064 fc->low_water = fc->high_water - 8;
4065 break;
4066 case e1000_pchlan:
4067 /* Workaround PCH LOM adapter hangs with certain network
4068 * loads. If hangs persist, try disabling Tx flow control.
4069 */
4070 if (adapter->netdev->mtu > ETH_DATA_LEN) {
4071 fc->high_water = 0x3500;
4072 fc->low_water = 0x1500;
4073 } else {
4074 fc->high_water = 0x5000;
4075 fc->low_water = 0x3000;
4076 }
4077 fc->refresh_time = 0x1000;
4078 break;
4079 case e1000_pch2lan:
4080 case e1000_pch_lpt:
4081 case e1000_pch_spt:
4082 case e1000_pch_cnp:
4083 fc->refresh_time = 0x0400;
4084
4085 if (adapter->netdev->mtu <= ETH_DATA_LEN) {
4086 fc->high_water = 0x05C20;
4087 fc->low_water = 0x05048;
4088 fc->pause_time = 0x0650;
4089 break;
4090 }
4091
4092 pba = 14;
4093 ew32(PBA, pba);
4094 fc->high_water = ((pba << 10) * 9 / 10) & E1000_FCRTH_RTH;
4095 fc->low_water = ((pba << 10) * 8 / 10) & E1000_FCRTL_RTL;
4096 break;
4097 }
4098
4099 /* Alignment of Tx data is on an arbitrary byte boundary with the
4100 * maximum size per Tx descriptor limited only to the transmit
4101 * allocation of the packet buffer minus 96 bytes with an upper
4102 * limit of 24KB due to receive synchronization limitations.
4103 */
4104 adapter->tx_fifo_limit = min_t(u32, ((er32(PBA) >> 16) << 10) - 96,
4105 24 << 10);
4106
4107 /* Disable Adaptive Interrupt Moderation if 2 full packets cannot
4108 * fit in receive buffer.
4109 */
4110 if (adapter->itr_setting & 0x3) {
4111 if ((adapter->max_frame_size * 2) > (pba << 10)) {
4112 if (!(adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_DISABLE_AIM)) {
4113 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev,
4114 "Interrupt Throttle Rate off\n");
4115 adapter->flags2 |= FLAG2_DISABLE_AIM;
4116 e1000e_write_itr(adapter, 0);
4117 }
4118 } else if (adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_DISABLE_AIM) {
4119 dev_info(&adapter->pdev->dev,
4120 "Interrupt Throttle Rate on\n");
4121 adapter->flags2 &= ~FLAG2_DISABLE_AIM;
4122 adapter->itr = 20000;
4123 e1000e_write_itr(adapter, adapter->itr);
4124 }
4125 }
4126
4127 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_pch_spt)
4128 e1000_flush_desc_rings(adapter);
4129 /* Allow time for pending master requests to run */
4130 mac->ops.reset_hw(hw);
4131
4132 /* For parts with AMT enabled, let the firmware know
4133 * that the network interface is in control
4134 */
4135 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_AMT)
4136 e1000e_get_hw_control(adapter);
4137
4138 ew32(WUC, 0);
4139
4140 if (mac->ops.init_hw(hw))
4141 e_err("Hardware Error\n");
4142
4143 e1000_update_mng_vlan(adapter);
4144
4145 /* Enable h/w to recognize an 802.1Q VLAN Ethernet packet */
4146 ew32(VET, ETH_P_8021Q);
4147
4148 e1000e_reset_adaptive(hw);
4149
4150 /* restore systim and hwtstamp settings */
4151 e1000e_systim_reset(adapter);
4152
4153 /* Set EEE advertisement as appropriate */
4154 if (adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_HAS_EEE) {
4155 s32 ret_val;
4156 u16 adv_addr;
4157
4158 switch (hw->phy.type) {
4159 case e1000_phy_82579:
4160 adv_addr = I82579_EEE_ADVERTISEMENT;
4161 break;
4162 case e1000_phy_i217:
4163 adv_addr = I217_EEE_ADVERTISEMENT;
4164 break;
4165 default:
4166 dev_err(&adapter->pdev->dev,
4167 "Invalid PHY type setting EEE advertisement\n");
4168 return;
4169 }
4170
4171 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.acquire(hw);
4172 if (ret_val) {
4173 dev_err(&adapter->pdev->dev,
4174 "EEE advertisement - unable to acquire PHY\n");
4175 return;
4176 }
4177
4178 e1000_write_emi_reg_locked(hw, adv_addr,
4179 hw->dev_spec.ich8lan.eee_disable ?
4180 0 : adapter->eee_advert);
4181
4182 hw->phy.ops.release(hw);
4183 }
4184
4185 if (!netif_running(adapter->netdev) &&
4186 !test_bit(__E1000_TESTING, &adapter->state))
4187 e1000_power_down_phy(adapter);
4188
4189 e1000_get_phy_info(hw);
4190
4191 if ((adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_SMART_POWER_DOWN) &&
4192 !(adapter->flags & FLAG_SMART_POWER_DOWN)) {
4193 u16 phy_data = 0;
4194 /* speed up time to link by disabling smart power down, ignore
4195 * the return value of this function because there is nothing
4196 * different we would do if it failed
4197 */
4198 e1e_rphy(hw, IGP02E1000_PHY_POWER_MGMT, &phy_data);
4199 phy_data &= ~IGP02E1000_PM_SPD;
4200 e1e_wphy(hw, IGP02E1000_PHY_POWER_MGMT, phy_data);
4201 }
4202 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_pch_spt && adapter->int_mode == 0) {
4203 u32 reg;
4204
4205 /* Fextnvm7 @ 0xe4[2] = 1 */
4206 reg = er32(FEXTNVM7);
4207 reg |= E1000_FEXTNVM7_SIDE_CLK_UNGATE;
4208 ew32(FEXTNVM7, reg);
4209 /* Fextnvm9 @ 0x5bb4[13:12] = 11 */
4210 reg = er32(FEXTNVM9);
4211 reg |= E1000_FEXTNVM9_IOSFSB_CLKGATE_DIS |
4212 E1000_FEXTNVM9_IOSFSB_CLKREQ_DIS;
4213 ew32(FEXTNVM9, reg);
4214 }
4215
4216}
4217
4218/**
4219 * e1000e_trigger_lsc - trigger an LSC interrupt
4220 * @adapter:
4221 *
4222 * Fire a link status change interrupt to start the watchdog.
4223 **/
4224static void e1000e_trigger_lsc(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
4225{
4226 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4227
4228 if (adapter->msix_entries)
4229 ew32(ICS, E1000_ICS_LSC | E1000_ICS_OTHER);
4230 else
4231 ew32(ICS, E1000_ICS_LSC);
4232}
4233
4234void e1000e_up(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
4235{
4236 /* hardware has been reset, we need to reload some things */
4237 e1000_configure(adapter);
4238
4239 clear_bit(__E1000_DOWN, &adapter->state);
4240
4241 if (adapter->msix_entries)
4242 e1000_configure_msix(adapter);
4243 e1000_irq_enable(adapter);
4244
4245 netif_start_queue(adapter->netdev);
4246
4247 e1000e_trigger_lsc(adapter);
4248}
4249
4250static void e1000e_flush_descriptors(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
4251{
4252 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4253
4254 if (!(adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_DMA_BURST))
4255 return;
4256
4257 /* flush pending descriptor writebacks to memory */
4258 ew32(TIDV, adapter->tx_int_delay | E1000_TIDV_FPD);
4259 ew32(RDTR, adapter->rx_int_delay | E1000_RDTR_FPD);
4260
4261 /* execute the writes immediately */
4262 e1e_flush();
4263
4264 /* due to rare timing issues, write to TIDV/RDTR again to ensure the
4265 * write is successful
4266 */
4267 ew32(TIDV, adapter->tx_int_delay | E1000_TIDV_FPD);
4268 ew32(RDTR, adapter->rx_int_delay | E1000_RDTR_FPD);
4269
4270 /* execute the writes immediately */
4271 e1e_flush();
4272}
4273
4274static void e1000e_update_stats(struct e1000_adapter *adapter);
4275
4276/**
4277 * e1000e_down - quiesce the device and optionally reset the hardware
4278 * @adapter: board private structure
4279 * @reset: boolean flag to reset the hardware or not
4280 */
4281void e1000e_down(struct e1000_adapter *adapter, bool reset)
4282{
4283 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
4284 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4285 u32 tctl, rctl;
4286
4287 /* signal that we're down so the interrupt handler does not
4288 * reschedule our watchdog timer
4289 */
4290 set_bit(__E1000_DOWN, &adapter->state);
4291
4292 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
4293
4294 /* disable receives in the hardware */
4295 rctl = er32(RCTL);
4296 if (!(adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_NO_DISABLE_RX))
4297 ew32(RCTL, rctl & ~E1000_RCTL_EN);
4298 /* flush and sleep below */
4299
4300 netif_stop_queue(netdev);
4301
4302 /* disable transmits in the hardware */
4303 tctl = er32(TCTL);
4304 tctl &= ~E1000_TCTL_EN;
4305 ew32(TCTL, tctl);
4306
4307 /* flush both disables and wait for them to finish */
4308 e1e_flush();
4309 usleep_range(10000, 20000);
4310
4311 e1000_irq_disable(adapter);
4312
4313 napi_synchronize(&adapter->napi);
4314
4315 del_timer_sync(&adapter->watchdog_timer);
4316 del_timer_sync(&adapter->phy_info_timer);
4317
4318 spin_lock(&adapter->stats64_lock);
4319 e1000e_update_stats(adapter);
4320 spin_unlock(&adapter->stats64_lock);
4321
4322 e1000e_flush_descriptors(adapter);
4323
4324 adapter->link_speed = 0;
4325 adapter->link_duplex = 0;
4326
4327 /* Disable Si errata workaround on PCHx for jumbo frame flow */
4328 if ((hw->mac.type >= e1000_pch2lan) &&
4329 (adapter->netdev->mtu > ETH_DATA_LEN) &&
4330 e1000_lv_jumbo_workaround_ich8lan(hw, false))
4331 e_dbg("failed to disable jumbo frame workaround mode\n");
4332
4333 if (!pci_channel_offline(adapter->pdev)) {
4334 if (reset)
4335 e1000e_reset(adapter);
4336 else if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_pch_spt)
4337 e1000_flush_desc_rings(adapter);
4338 }
4339 e1000_clean_tx_ring(adapter->tx_ring);
4340 e1000_clean_rx_ring(adapter->rx_ring);
4341}
4342
4343void e1000e_reinit_locked(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
4344{
4345 might_sleep();
4346 while (test_and_set_bit(__E1000_RESETTING, &adapter->state))
4347 usleep_range(1000, 2000);
4348 e1000e_down(adapter, true);
4349 e1000e_up(adapter);
4350 clear_bit(__E1000_RESETTING, &adapter->state);
4351}
4352
4353/**
4354 * e1000e_sanitize_systim - sanitize raw cycle counter reads
4355 * @hw: pointer to the HW structure
4356 * @systim: time value read, sanitized and returned
4357 *
4358 * Errata for 82574/82583 possible bad bits read from SYSTIMH/L:
4359 * check to see that the time is incrementing at a reasonable
4360 * rate and is a multiple of incvalue.
4361 **/
4362static u64 e1000e_sanitize_systim(struct e1000_hw *hw, u64 systim)
4363{
4364 u64 time_delta, rem, temp;
4365 u64 systim_next;
4366 u32 incvalue;
4367 int i;
4368
4369 incvalue = er32(TIMINCA) & E1000_TIMINCA_INCVALUE_MASK;
4370 for (i = 0; i < E1000_MAX_82574_SYSTIM_REREADS; i++) {
4371 /* latch SYSTIMH on read of SYSTIML */
4372 systim_next = (u64)er32(SYSTIML);
4373 systim_next |= (u64)er32(SYSTIMH) << 32;
4374
4375 time_delta = systim_next - systim;
4376 temp = time_delta;
4377 /* VMWare users have seen incvalue of zero, don't div / 0 */
4378 rem = incvalue ? do_div(temp, incvalue) : (time_delta != 0);
4379
4380 systim = systim_next;
4381
4382 if ((time_delta < E1000_82574_SYSTIM_EPSILON) && (rem == 0))
4383 break;
4384 }
4385
4386 return systim;
4387}
4388
4389/**
4390 * e1000e_cyclecounter_read - read raw cycle counter (used by time counter)
4391 * @cc: cyclecounter structure
4392 **/
4393static u64 e1000e_cyclecounter_read(const struct cyclecounter *cc)
4394{
4395 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = container_of(cc, struct e1000_adapter,
4396 cc);
4397 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4398 u32 systimel, systimeh;
4399 u64 systim;
4400 /* SYSTIMH latching upon SYSTIML read does not work well.
4401 * This means that if SYSTIML overflows after we read it but before
4402 * we read SYSTIMH, the value of SYSTIMH has been incremented and we
4403 * will experience a huge non linear increment in the systime value
4404 * to fix that we test for overflow and if true, we re-read systime.
4405 */
4406 systimel = er32(SYSTIML);
4407 systimeh = er32(SYSTIMH);
4408 /* Is systimel is so large that overflow is possible? */
4409 if (systimel >= (u32)0xffffffff - E1000_TIMINCA_INCVALUE_MASK) {
4410 u32 systimel_2 = er32(SYSTIML);
4411 if (systimel > systimel_2) {
4412 /* There was an overflow, read again SYSTIMH, and use
4413 * systimel_2
4414 */
4415 systimeh = er32(SYSTIMH);
4416 systimel = systimel_2;
4417 }
4418 }
4419 systim = (u64)systimel;
4420 systim |= (u64)systimeh << 32;
4421
4422 if (adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_CHECK_SYSTIM_OVERFLOW)
4423 systim = e1000e_sanitize_systim(hw, systim);
4424
4425 return systim;
4426}
4427
4428/**
4429 * e1000_sw_init - Initialize general software structures (struct e1000_adapter)
4430 * @adapter: board private structure to initialize
4431 *
4432 * e1000_sw_init initializes the Adapter private data structure.
4433 * Fields are initialized based on PCI device information and
4434 * OS network device settings (MTU size).
4435 **/
4436static int e1000_sw_init(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
4437{
4438 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
4439
4440 adapter->rx_buffer_len = VLAN_ETH_FRAME_LEN + ETH_FCS_LEN;
4441 adapter->rx_ps_bsize0 = 128;
4442 adapter->max_frame_size = netdev->mtu + VLAN_ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN;
4443 adapter->min_frame_size = ETH_ZLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN;
4444 adapter->tx_ring_count = E1000_DEFAULT_TXD;
4445 adapter->rx_ring_count = E1000_DEFAULT_RXD;
4446
4447 spin_lock_init(&adapter->stats64_lock);
4448
4449 e1000e_set_interrupt_capability(adapter);
4450
4451 if (e1000_alloc_queues(adapter))
4452 return -ENOMEM;
4453
4454 /* Setup hardware time stamping cyclecounter */
4455 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_HW_TIMESTAMP) {
4456 adapter->cc.read = e1000e_cyclecounter_read;
4457 adapter->cc.mask = CYCLECOUNTER_MASK(64);
4458 adapter->cc.mult = 1;
4459 /* cc.shift set in e1000e_get_base_tininca() */
4460
4461 spin_lock_init(&adapter->systim_lock);
4462 INIT_WORK(&adapter->tx_hwtstamp_work, e1000e_tx_hwtstamp_work);
4463 }
4464
4465 /* Explicitly disable IRQ since the NIC can be in any state. */
4466 e1000_irq_disable(adapter);
4467
4468 set_bit(__E1000_DOWN, &adapter->state);
4469 return 0;
4470}
4471
4472/**
4473 * e1000_intr_msi_test - Interrupt Handler
4474 * @irq: interrupt number
4475 * @data: pointer to a network interface device structure
4476 **/
4477static irqreturn_t e1000_intr_msi_test(int __always_unused irq, void *data)
4478{
4479 struct net_device *netdev = data;
4480 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4481 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4482 u32 icr = er32(ICR);
4483
4484 e_dbg("icr is %08X\n", icr);
4485 if (icr & E1000_ICR_RXSEQ) {
4486 adapter->flags &= ~FLAG_MSI_TEST_FAILED;
4487 /* Force memory writes to complete before acknowledging the
4488 * interrupt is handled.
4489 */
4490 wmb();
4491 }
4492
4493 return IRQ_HANDLED;
4494}
4495
4496/**
4497 * e1000_test_msi_interrupt - Returns 0 for successful test
4498 * @adapter: board private struct
4499 *
4500 * code flow taken from tg3.c
4501 **/
4502static int e1000_test_msi_interrupt(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
4503{
4504 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
4505 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4506 int err;
4507
4508 /* poll_enable hasn't been called yet, so don't need disable */
4509 /* clear any pending events */
4510 er32(ICR);
4511
4512 /* free the real vector and request a test handler */
4513 e1000_free_irq(adapter);
4514 e1000e_reset_interrupt_capability(adapter);
4515
4516 /* Assume that the test fails, if it succeeds then the test
4517 * MSI irq handler will unset this flag
4518 */
4519 adapter->flags |= FLAG_MSI_TEST_FAILED;
4520
4521 err = pci_enable_msi(adapter->pdev);
4522 if (err)
4523 goto msi_test_failed;
4524
4525 err = request_irq(adapter->pdev->irq, e1000_intr_msi_test, 0,
4526 netdev->name, netdev);
4527 if (err) {
4528 pci_disable_msi(adapter->pdev);
4529 goto msi_test_failed;
4530 }
4531
4532 /* Force memory writes to complete before enabling and firing an
4533 * interrupt.
4534 */
4535 wmb();
4536
4537 e1000_irq_enable(adapter);
4538
4539 /* fire an unusual interrupt on the test handler */
4540 ew32(ICS, E1000_ICS_RXSEQ);
4541 e1e_flush();
4542 msleep(100);
4543
4544 e1000_irq_disable(adapter);
4545
4546 rmb(); /* read flags after interrupt has been fired */
4547
4548 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_MSI_TEST_FAILED) {
4549 adapter->int_mode = E1000E_INT_MODE_LEGACY;
4550 e_info("MSI interrupt test failed, using legacy interrupt.\n");
4551 } else {
4552 e_dbg("MSI interrupt test succeeded!\n");
4553 }
4554
4555 free_irq(adapter->pdev->irq, netdev);
4556 pci_disable_msi(adapter->pdev);
4557
4558msi_test_failed:
4559 e1000e_set_interrupt_capability(adapter);
4560 return e1000_request_irq(adapter);
4561}
4562
4563/**
4564 * e1000_test_msi - Returns 0 if MSI test succeeds or INTx mode is restored
4565 * @adapter: board private struct
4566 *
4567 * code flow taken from tg3.c, called with e1000 interrupts disabled.
4568 **/
4569static int e1000_test_msi(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
4570{
4571 int err;
4572 u16 pci_cmd;
4573
4574 if (!(adapter->flags & FLAG_MSI_ENABLED))
4575 return 0;
4576
4577 /* disable SERR in case the MSI write causes a master abort */
4578 pci_read_config_word(adapter->pdev, PCI_COMMAND, &pci_cmd);
4579 if (pci_cmd & PCI_COMMAND_SERR)
4580 pci_write_config_word(adapter->pdev, PCI_COMMAND,
4581 pci_cmd & ~PCI_COMMAND_SERR);
4582
4583 err = e1000_test_msi_interrupt(adapter);
4584
4585 /* re-enable SERR */
4586 if (pci_cmd & PCI_COMMAND_SERR) {
4587 pci_read_config_word(adapter->pdev, PCI_COMMAND, &pci_cmd);
4588 pci_cmd |= PCI_COMMAND_SERR;
4589 pci_write_config_word(adapter->pdev, PCI_COMMAND, pci_cmd);
4590 }
4591
4592 return err;
4593}
4594
4595/**
4596 * e1000e_open - Called when a network interface is made active
4597 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4598 *
4599 * Returns 0 on success, negative value on failure
4600 *
4601 * The open entry point is called when a network interface is made
4602 * active by the system (IFF_UP). At this point all resources needed
4603 * for transmit and receive operations are allocated, the interrupt
4604 * handler is registered with the OS, the watchdog timer is started,
4605 * and the stack is notified that the interface is ready.
4606 **/
4607int e1000e_open(struct net_device *netdev)
4608{
4609 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4610 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4611 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
4612 int err;
4613
4614 /* disallow open during test */
4615 if (test_bit(__E1000_TESTING, &adapter->state))
4616 return -EBUSY;
4617
4618 pm_runtime_get_sync(&pdev->dev);
4619
4620 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
4621
4622 /* allocate transmit descriptors */
4623 err = e1000e_setup_tx_resources(adapter->tx_ring);
4624 if (err)
4625 goto err_setup_tx;
4626
4627 /* allocate receive descriptors */
4628 err = e1000e_setup_rx_resources(adapter->rx_ring);
4629 if (err)
4630 goto err_setup_rx;
4631
4632 /* If AMT is enabled, let the firmware know that the network
4633 * interface is now open and reset the part to a known state.
4634 */
4635 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_AMT) {
4636 e1000e_get_hw_control(adapter);
4637 e1000e_reset(adapter);
4638 }
4639
4640 e1000e_power_up_phy(adapter);
4641
4642 adapter->mng_vlan_id = E1000_MNG_VLAN_NONE;
4643 if ((adapter->hw.mng_cookie.status & E1000_MNG_DHCP_COOKIE_STATUS_VLAN))
4644 e1000_update_mng_vlan(adapter);
4645
4646 /* DMA latency requirement to workaround jumbo issue */
4647 pm_qos_add_request(&adapter->pm_qos_req, PM_QOS_CPU_DMA_LATENCY,
4648 PM_QOS_DEFAULT_VALUE);
4649
4650 /* before we allocate an interrupt, we must be ready to handle it.
4651 * Setting DEBUG_SHIRQ in the kernel makes it fire an interrupt
4652 * as soon as we call pci_request_irq, so we have to setup our
4653 * clean_rx handler before we do so.
4654 */
4655 e1000_configure(adapter);
4656
4657 err = e1000_request_irq(adapter);
4658 if (err)
4659 goto err_req_irq;
4660
4661 /* Work around PCIe errata with MSI interrupts causing some chipsets to
4662 * ignore e1000e MSI messages, which means we need to test our MSI
4663 * interrupt now
4664 */
4665 if (adapter->int_mode != E1000E_INT_MODE_LEGACY) {
4666 err = e1000_test_msi(adapter);
4667 if (err) {
4668 e_err("Interrupt allocation failed\n");
4669 goto err_req_irq;
4670 }
4671 }
4672
4673 /* From here on the code is the same as e1000e_up() */
4674 clear_bit(__E1000_DOWN, &adapter->state);
4675
4676 napi_enable(&adapter->napi);
4677
4678 e1000_irq_enable(adapter);
4679
4680 adapter->tx_hang_recheck = false;
4681 netif_start_queue(netdev);
4682
4683 hw->mac.get_link_status = true;
4684 pm_runtime_put(&pdev->dev);
4685
4686 e1000e_trigger_lsc(adapter);
4687
4688 return 0;
4689
4690err_req_irq:
4691 pm_qos_remove_request(&adapter->pm_qos_req);
4692 e1000e_release_hw_control(adapter);
4693 e1000_power_down_phy(adapter);
4694 e1000e_free_rx_resources(adapter->rx_ring);
4695err_setup_rx:
4696 e1000e_free_tx_resources(adapter->tx_ring);
4697err_setup_tx:
4698 e1000e_reset(adapter);
4699 pm_runtime_put_sync(&pdev->dev);
4700
4701 return err;
4702}
4703
4704/**
4705 * e1000e_close - Disables a network interface
4706 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4707 *
4708 * Returns 0, this is not allowed to fail
4709 *
4710 * The close entry point is called when an interface is de-activated
4711 * by the OS. The hardware is still under the drivers control, but
4712 * needs to be disabled. A global MAC reset is issued to stop the
4713 * hardware, and all transmit and receive resources are freed.
4714 **/
4715int e1000e_close(struct net_device *netdev)
4716{
4717 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4718 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
4719 int count = E1000_CHECK_RESET_COUNT;
4720
4721 while (test_bit(__E1000_RESETTING, &adapter->state) && count--)
4722 usleep_range(10000, 20000);
4723
4724 WARN_ON(test_bit(__E1000_RESETTING, &adapter->state));
4725
4726 pm_runtime_get_sync(&pdev->dev);
4727
4728 if (!test_bit(__E1000_DOWN, &adapter->state)) {
4729 e1000e_down(adapter, true);
4730 e1000_free_irq(adapter);
4731
4732 /* Link status message must follow this format */
4733 pr_info("%s NIC Link is Down\n", adapter->netdev->name);
4734 }
4735
4736 napi_disable(&adapter->napi);
4737
4738 e1000e_free_tx_resources(adapter->tx_ring);
4739 e1000e_free_rx_resources(adapter->rx_ring);
4740
4741 /* kill manageability vlan ID if supported, but not if a vlan with
4742 * the same ID is registered on the host OS (let 8021q kill it)
4743 */
4744 if (adapter->hw.mng_cookie.status & E1000_MNG_DHCP_COOKIE_STATUS_VLAN)
4745 e1000_vlan_rx_kill_vid(netdev, htons(ETH_P_8021Q),
4746 adapter->mng_vlan_id);
4747
4748 /* If AMT is enabled, let the firmware know that the network
4749 * interface is now closed
4750 */
4751 if ((adapter->flags & FLAG_HAS_AMT) &&
4752 !test_bit(__E1000_TESTING, &adapter->state))
4753 e1000e_release_hw_control(adapter);
4754
4755 pm_qos_remove_request(&adapter->pm_qos_req);
4756
4757 pm_runtime_put_sync(&pdev->dev);
4758
4759 return 0;
4760}
4761
4762/**
4763 * e1000_set_mac - Change the Ethernet Address of the NIC
4764 * @netdev: network interface device structure
4765 * @p: pointer to an address structure
4766 *
4767 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
4768 **/
4769static int e1000_set_mac(struct net_device *netdev, void *p)
4770{
4771 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(netdev);
4772 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4773 struct sockaddr *addr = p;
4774
4775 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(addr->sa_data))
4776 return -EADDRNOTAVAIL;
4777
4778 memcpy(netdev->dev_addr, addr->sa_data, netdev->addr_len);
4779 memcpy(adapter->hw.mac.addr, addr->sa_data, netdev->addr_len);
4780
4781 hw->mac.ops.rar_set(&adapter->hw, adapter->hw.mac.addr, 0);
4782
4783 if (adapter->flags & FLAG_RESET_OVERWRITES_LAA) {
4784 /* activate the work around */
4785 e1000e_set_laa_state_82571(&adapter->hw, 1);
4786
4787 /* Hold a copy of the LAA in RAR[14] This is done so that
4788 * between the time RAR[0] gets clobbered and the time it
4789 * gets fixed (in e1000_watchdog), the actual LAA is in one
4790 * of the RARs and no incoming packets directed to this port
4791 * are dropped. Eventually the LAA will be in RAR[0] and
4792 * RAR[14]
4793 */
4794 hw->mac.ops.rar_set(&adapter->hw, adapter->hw.mac.addr,
4795 adapter->hw.mac.rar_entry_count - 1);
4796 }
4797
4798 return 0;
4799}
4800
4801/**
4802 * e1000e_update_phy_task - work thread to update phy
4803 * @work: pointer to our work struct
4804 *
4805 * this worker thread exists because we must acquire a
4806 * semaphore to read the phy, which we could msleep while
4807 * waiting for it, and we can't msleep in a timer.
4808 **/
4809static void e1000e_update_phy_task(struct work_struct *work)
4810{
4811 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = container_of(work,
4812 struct e1000_adapter,
4813 update_phy_task);
4814 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4815
4816 if (test_bit(__E1000_DOWN, &adapter->state))
4817 return;
4818
4819 e1000_get_phy_info(hw);
4820
4821 /* Enable EEE on 82579 after link up */
4822 if (hw->phy.type >= e1000_phy_82579)
4823 e1000_set_eee_pchlan(hw);
4824}
4825
4826/**
4827 * e1000_update_phy_info - timre call-back to update PHY info
4828 * @data: pointer to adapter cast into an unsigned long
4829 *
4830 * Need to wait a few seconds after link up to get diagnostic information from
4831 * the phy
4832 **/
4833static void e1000_update_phy_info(unsigned long data)
4834{
4835 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = (struct e1000_adapter *)data;
4836
4837 if (test_bit(__E1000_DOWN, &adapter->state))
4838 return;
4839
4840 schedule_work(&adapter->update_phy_task);
4841}
4842
4843/**
4844 * e1000e_update_phy_stats - Update the PHY statistics counters
4845 * @adapter: board private structure
4846 *
4847 * Read/clear the upper 16-bit PHY registers and read/accumulate lower
4848 **/
4849static void e1000e_update_phy_stats(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
4850{
4851 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4852 s32 ret_val;
4853 u16 phy_data;
4854
4855 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.acquire(hw);
4856 if (ret_val)
4857 return;
4858
4859 /* A page set is expensive so check if already on desired page.
4860 * If not, set to the page with the PHY status registers.
4861 */
4862 hw->phy.addr = 1;
4863 ret_val = e1000e_read_phy_reg_mdic(hw, IGP01E1000_PHY_PAGE_SELECT,
4864 &phy_data);
4865 if (ret_val)
4866 goto release;
4867 if (phy_data != (HV_STATS_PAGE << IGP_PAGE_SHIFT)) {
4868 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.set_page(hw,
4869 HV_STATS_PAGE << IGP_PAGE_SHIFT);
4870 if (ret_val)
4871 goto release;
4872 }
4873
4874 /* Single Collision Count */
4875 hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_SCC_UPPER, &phy_data);
4876 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_SCC_LOWER, &phy_data);
4877 if (!ret_val)
4878 adapter->stats.scc += phy_data;
4879
4880 /* Excessive Collision Count */
4881 hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_ECOL_UPPER, &phy_data);
4882 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_ECOL_LOWER, &phy_data);
4883 if (!ret_val)
4884 adapter->stats.ecol += phy_data;
4885
4886 /* Multiple Collision Count */
4887 hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_MCC_UPPER, &phy_data);
4888 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_MCC_LOWER, &phy_data);
4889 if (!ret_val)
4890 adapter->stats.mcc += phy_data;
4891
4892 /* Late Collision Count */
4893 hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_LATECOL_UPPER, &phy_data);
4894 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_LATECOL_LOWER, &phy_data);
4895 if (!ret_val)
4896 adapter->stats.latecol += phy_data;
4897
4898 /* Collision Count - also used for adaptive IFS */
4899 hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_COLC_UPPER, &phy_data);
4900 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_COLC_LOWER, &phy_data);
4901 if (!ret_val)
4902 hw->mac.collision_delta = phy_data;
4903
4904 /* Defer Count */
4905 hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_DC_UPPER, &phy_data);
4906 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_DC_LOWER, &phy_data);
4907 if (!ret_val)
4908 adapter->stats.dc += phy_data;
4909
4910 /* Transmit with no CRS */
4911 hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_TNCRS_UPPER, &phy_data);
4912 ret_val = hw->phy.ops.read_reg_page(hw, HV_TNCRS_LOWER, &phy_data);
4913 if (!ret_val)
4914 adapter->stats.tncrs += phy_data;
4915
4916release:
4917 hw->phy.ops.release(hw);
4918}
4919
4920/**
4921 * e1000e_update_stats - Update the board statistics counters
4922 * @adapter: board private structure
4923 **/
4924static void e1000e_update_stats(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
4925{
4926 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
4927 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
4928 struct pci_dev *pdev = adapter->pdev;
4929
4930 /* Prevent stats update while adapter is being reset, or if the pci
4931 * connection is down.
4932 */
4933 if (adapter->link_speed == 0)
4934 return;
4935 if (pci_channel_offline(pdev))
4936 return;
4937
4938 adapter->stats.crcerrs += er32(CRCERRS);
4939 adapter->stats.gprc += er32(GPRC);
4940 adapter->stats.gorc += er32(GORCL);
4941 er32(GORCH); /* Clear gorc */
4942 adapter->stats.bprc += er32(BPRC);
4943 adapter->stats.mprc += er32(MPRC);
4944 adapter->stats.roc += er32(ROC);
4945
4946 adapter->stats.mpc += er32(MPC);
4947
4948 /* Half-duplex statistics */
4949 if (adapter->link_duplex == HALF_DUPLEX) {
4950 if (adapter->flags2 & FLAG2_HAS_PHY_STATS) {
4951 e1000e_update_phy_stats(adapter);
4952 } else {
4953 adapter->stats.scc += er32(SCC);
4954 adapter->stats.ecol += er32(ECOL);
4955 adapter->stats.mcc += er32(MCC);
4956 adapter->stats.latecol += er32(LATECOL);
4957 adapter->stats.dc += er32(DC);
4958
4959 hw->mac.collision_delta = er32(COLC);
4960
4961 if ((hw->mac.type != e1000_82574) &&
4962 (hw->mac.type != e1000_82583))
4963 adapter->stats.tncrs += er32(TNCRS);
4964 }
4965 adapter->stats.colc += hw->mac.collision_delta;
4966 }
4967
4968 adapter->stats.xonrxc += er32(XONRXC);
4969 adapter->stats.xontxc += er32(XONTXC);
4970 adapter->stats.xoffrxc += er32(XOFFRXC);
4971 adapter->stats.xofftxc += er32(XOFFTXC);
4972 adapter->stats.gptc += er32(GPTC);
4973 adapter->stats.gotc += er32(GOTCL);
4974 er32(GOTCH); /* Clear gotc */
4975 adapter->stats.rnbc += er32(RNBC);
4976 adapter->stats.ruc += er32(RUC);
4977
4978 adapter->stats.mptc += er32(MPTC);
4979 adapter->stats.bptc += er32(BPTC);
4980
4981 /* used for adaptive IFS */
4982
4983 hw->mac.tx_packet_delta = er32(TPT);
4984 adapter->stats.tpt += hw->mac.tx_packet_delta;
4985
4986 adapter->stats.algnerrc += er32(ALGNERRC);
4987 adapter->stats.rxerrc += er32(RXERRC);
4988 adapter->stats.cexterr += er32(CEXTERR);
4989 adapter->stats.tsctc += er32(TSCTC);
4990 adapter->stats.tsctfc += er32(TSCTFC);
4991
4992 /* Fill out the OS statistics structure */
4993 netdev->stats.multicast = adapter->stats.mprc;
4994 netdev->stats.collisions = adapter->stats.colc;
4995
4996 /* Rx Errors */
4997
4998 /* RLEC on some newer hardware can be incorrect so build
4999 * our own version based on RUC and ROC
5000 */
5001 netdev->stats.rx_errors = adapter->stats.rxerrc +
5002 adapter->stats.crcerrs + adapter->stats.algnerrc +
5003 adapter->stats.ruc + adapter->stats.roc + adapter->stats.cexterr;
5004 netdev->stats.rx_length_errors = adapter->stats.ruc +
5005 adapter->stats.roc;
5006 netdev->stats.rx_crc_errors = adapter->stats.crcerrs;
5007 netdev->stats.rx_frame_errors = adapter->stats.algnerrc;
5008 netdev->stats.rx_missed_errors = adapter->stats.mpc;
5009
5010 /* Tx Errors */
5011 netdev->stats.tx_errors = adapter->stats.ecol + adapter->stats.latecol;
5012 netdev->stats.tx_aborted_errors = adapter->stats.ecol;
5013 netdev->stats.tx_window_errors = adapter->stats.latecol;
5014 netdev->stats.tx_carrier_errors = adapter->stats.tncrs;
5015
5016 /* Tx Dropped needs to be maintained elsewhere */
5017
5018 /* Management Stats */
5019 adapter->stats.mgptc += er32(MGTPTC);
5020 adapter->stats.mgprc += er32(MGTPRC);
5021 adapter->stats.mgpdc += er32(MGTPDC);
5022
5023 /* Correctable ECC Errors */
5024 if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_pch_lpt) {
5025 u32 pbeccsts = er32(PBECCSTS);
5026
5027 adapter->corr_errors +=
5028 pbeccsts & E1000_PBECCSTS_CORR_ERR_CNT_MASK;
5029 adapter->uncorr_errors +=
5030 (pbeccsts & E1000_PBECCSTS_UNCORR_ERR_CNT_MASK) >>
5031 E1000_PBECCSTS_UNCORR_ERR_CNT_SHIFT;
5032 }
5033}
5034
5035/**
5036 * e1000_phy_read_status - Update the PHY register status snapshot
5037 * @adapter: board private structure
5038 **/
5039static void e1000_phy_read_status(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
5040{
5041 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5042 struct e1000_phy_regs *phy = &adapter->phy_regs;
5043
5044 if (!pm_runtime_suspended((&adapter->pdev->dev)->parent) &&
5045 (er32(STATUS) & E1000_STATUS_LU) &&
5046 (adapter->hw.phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_copper)) {
5047 int ret_val;
5048
5049 ret_val = e1e_rphy(hw, MII_BMCR, &phy->bmcr);
5050 ret_val |= e1e_rphy(hw, MII_BMSR, &phy->bmsr);
5051 ret_val |= e1e_rphy(hw, MII_ADVERTISE, &phy->advertise);
5052 ret_val |= e1e_rphy(hw, MII_LPA, &phy->lpa);
5053 ret_val |= e1e_rphy(hw, MII_EXPANSION, &phy->expansion);
5054 ret_val |= e1e_rphy(hw, MII_CTRL1000, &phy->ctrl1000);
5055 ret_val |= e1e_rphy(hw, MII_STAT1000, &phy->stat1000);
5056 ret_val |= e1e_rphy(hw, MII_ESTATUS, &phy->estatus);
5057 if (ret_val)
5058 e_warn("Error reading PHY register\n");
5059 } else {
5060 /* Do not read PHY registers if link is not up
5061 * Set values to typical power-on defaults
5062 */
5063 phy->bmcr = (BMCR_SPEED1000 | BMCR_ANENABLE | BMCR_FULLDPLX);
5064 phy->bmsr = (BMSR_100FULL | BMSR_100HALF | BMSR_10FULL |
5065 BMSR_10HALF | BMSR_ESTATEN | BMSR_ANEGCAPABLE |
5066 BMSR_ERCAP);
5067 phy->advertise = (ADVERTISE_PAUSE_ASYM | ADVERTISE_PAUSE_CAP |
5068 ADVERTISE_ALL | ADVERTISE_CSMA);
5069 phy->lpa = 0;
5070 phy->expansion = EXPANSION_ENABLENPAGE;
5071 phy->ctrl1000 = ADVERTISE_1000FULL;
5072 phy->stat1000 = 0;
5073 phy->estatus = (ESTATUS_1000_TFULL | ESTATUS_1000_THALF);
5074 }
5075}
5076
5077static void e1000_print_link_info(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
5078{
5079 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5080 u32 ctrl = er32(CTRL);
5081
5082 /* Link status message must follow this format for user tools */
5083 pr_info("%s NIC Link is Up %d Mbps %s Duplex, Flow Control: %s\n",
5084 adapter->netdev->name, adapter->link_speed,
5085 adapter->link_duplex == FULL_DUPLEX ? "Full" : "Half",
5086 (ctrl & E1000_CTRL_TFCE) && (ctrl & E1000_CTRL_RFCE) ? "Rx/Tx" :
5087 (ctrl & E1000_CTRL_RFCE) ? "Rx" :
5088 (ctrl & E1000_CTRL_TFCE) ? "Tx" : "None");
5089}
5090
5091static bool e1000e_has_link(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
5092{
5093 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5094 bool link_active = false;
5095 s32 ret_val = 0;
5096
5097 /* get_link_status is set on LSC (link status) interrupt or
5098 * Rx sequence error interrupt. get_link_status will stay
5099 * false until the check_for_link establishes link
5100 * for copper adapters ONLY
5101 */
5102 switch (hw->phy.media_type) {
5103 case e1000_media_type_copper:
5104 if (hw->mac.get_link_status) {
5105 ret_val = hw->mac.ops.check_for_link(hw);
5106 link_active = ret_val > 0;
5107 } else {
5108 link_active = true;
5109 }
5110 break;
5111 case e1000_media_type_fiber:
5112 ret_val = hw->mac.ops.check_for_link(hw);
5113 link_active = !!(er32(STATUS) & E1000_STATUS_LU);
5114 break;
5115 case e1000_media_type_internal_serdes:
5116 ret_val = hw->mac.ops.check_for_link(hw);
5117 link_active = adapter->hw.mac.serdes_has_link;
5118 break;
5119 default:
5120 case e1000_media_type_unknown:
5121 break;
5122 }
5123
5124 if ((ret_val == -E1000_ERR_PHY) && (hw->phy.type == e1000_phy_igp_3) &&
5125 (er32(CTRL) & E1000_PHY_CTRL_GBE_DISABLE)) {
5126 /* See e1000_kmrn_lock_loss_workaround_ich8lan() */
5127 e_info("Gigabit has been disabled, downgrading speed\n");
5128 }
5129
5130 return link_active;
5131}
5132
5133static void e1000e_enable_receives(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
5134{
5135 /* make sure the receive unit is started */
5136 if ((adapter->flags & FLAG_RX_NEEDS_RESTART) &&
5137 (adapter->flags & FLAG_RESTART_NOW)) {
5138 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5139 u32 rctl = er32(RCTL);
5140
5141 ew32(RCTL, rctl | E1000_RCTL_EN);
5142 adapter->flags &= ~FLAG_RESTART_NOW;
5143 }
5144}
5145
5146static void e1000e_check_82574_phy_workaround(struct e1000_adapter *adapter)
5147{
5148 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5149
5150 /* With 82574 controllers, PHY needs to be checked periodically
5151 * for hung state and reset, if two calls return true
5152 */
5153 if (e1000_check_phy_82574(hw))
5154 adapter->phy_hang_count++;
5155 else
5156 adapter->phy_hang_count = 0;
5157
5158 if (adapter->phy_hang_count > 1) {
5159 adapter->phy_hang_count = 0;
5160 e_dbg("PHY appears hung - resetting\n");
5161 schedule_work(&adapter->reset_task);
5162 }
5163}
5164
5165/**
5166 * e1000_watchdog - Timer Call-back
5167 * @data: pointer to adapter cast into an unsigned long
5168 **/
5169static void e1000_watchdog(unsigned long data)
5170{
5171 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = (struct e1000_adapter *)data;
5172
5173 /* Do the rest outside of interrupt context */
5174 schedule_work(&adapter->watchdog_task);
5175
5176 /* TODO: make this use queue_delayed_work() */
5177}
5178
5179static void e1000_watchdog_task(struct work_struct *work)
5180{
5181 struct e1000_adapter *adapter = container_of(work,
5182 struct e1000_adapter,
5183 watchdog_task);
5184 struct net_device *netdev = adapter->netdev;
5185 struct e1000_mac_info *mac = &adapter->hw.mac;
5186 struct e1000_phy_info *phy = &adapter->hw.phy;
5187 struct e1000_ring *tx_ring = adapter->tx_ring;
5188 struct e1000_hw *hw = &adapter->hw;
5189 u32 link, tctl;
5190
5191 if (test_bit(__E1000_DOWN, &adapter->state))
5192 return;
5193
5194 link = e1000e_has_link(adapter);
5195 if ((netif_carrier_ok(netdev)) && link) {
5196 /* Cancel scheduled suspend requests. */
5197 pm_runtime_resume(netdev->dev.parent);
5198
5199 e1000e_enable_receives(adapter);
5200 goto link_up;
5201 }
5202
5203 if ((e1000e_enable_tx_pkt_filtering(hw)) &&
5204 (adapter->mng_vlan_id != adapter->hw.mng_cookie.vlan_id))
5205 e1000_update_mng_vlan(adapter);
5206
5207 if (link) {
5208 if (!netif_carrier_ok(netdev)) {
5209 bool txb2b = true;
5210
